  "instructions": [
    "In a molcajete, mash the French lentils into a coarse paste.",
    "Mix in the pork fat, cheese, onion, garlic, egg, bread, salt, black pepper, and allspice until well combined.",
    "Cover the mixture and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes or overnight.",
    "Heat about 1/2 inch of lard or vegetable oil in a deep frying pan to 375\u00069F (190\u00063C).",
    "Using a spoon, drop small balls of the lentil mixture into the hot oil, about 1 tablespoon each.",
    "Fry the fritters for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until crispy and golden brown.",
    "Drain the fritters on paper towels and serve hot."
